cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper is about optimizing the hyperparameters of reservoir computers for forecasting chaotic systems. Reservoir computing is a subfield of machine learning and neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also uses Bayesian optimization, which is a popular optimization technique in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper deals with forecasting and control of chaotic systems, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also explores the design of simpler reservoir networks, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
